Program: Start the Week
Title: Torture, terrorism and secrets
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01nkwxc
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 29 Oct 2012
On Start the Week the journalist Ian Cobain reveals how torture has been systematically used by the British from WWII to the War on Terror, via Kenya and Northern Ireland. David Anderson QC reviews the risks posed by terrorism in the UK. Extraordinary rendition and the language of concealment form the heart of Clare Bayley's new play, and there are more secrets uncovered by the criminal barrister-turned-crime writer, MR Hall. Producer: Katy Hickman. Show less